  "prompt": "How do I do slow motion video with a Nikon D3100?",
  "response": "To create slow-motion video with a Nikon D3100, follow these steps:\n\n1. Video Capabilities:\n- The Nikon D3100 can record video at 24 fps (frames per second) at 1080p\n- For slow motion effect, you'll need to do post-production editing\n\n2. Recording Video:\n- Switch the mode dial to Live View/Video mode\n- Press the Live View button to start recording\n- Press the button again to stop recording\n\n3. Post-Production Slow Motion:\n- Use video editing software like:\n  * Windows Movie Maker\n  * Adobe Premiere\n  * Final Cut Pro\n  * iMovie\n\n4. Slow Motion Editing Process:\n- Import your video into editing software\n- Use the speed/duration settings\n- Reduce playback speed to 50% or lower\n- This will create a slow-motion effect\n\n5. Tips for Best Results:\n- Film at the highest frame rate possible\n- Use a tripod for stability\n- Ensure good lighting\n- Use faster shutter speeds\n\nNote: The D3100 has limited slow-motion capabilities compared to newer cameras, so post-production editing is key.",
